WEBVTT

00:02.830 --> 00:04.460
Dre: There are so many great
things about being black.

00:04.460 --> 00:05.920
We save money on suntan lotion.

00:05.920 --> 00:09.210
We look good,
even when we lose our hair.

00:09.210 --> 00:11.960
And we all know someone
who knows someone

00:11.960 --> 00:15.500
who knows someone
who knows Barack Obama.

00:15.500 --> 00:18.330
But as easy
as we seem to have it,

00:18.330 --> 00:21.830
we're twice as likely
to get diagnosed with diabetes.

00:21.830 --> 00:24.880
While genetics are a factor,
diabetes has also been linked

00:24.880 --> 00:28.830
to obesity, poor diet,
and inactivity.

00:28.830 --> 00:32.830
But don't get it twisted --
It's not all our fault.

00:32.830 --> 00:36.380
For a lot of us, it's hard to
be fit living in a food desert

00:36.380 --> 00:39.040
with no decent healthcare
or gyms.

00:39.040 --> 00:41.710
And let's be honest --
Who has time for exercise

00:41.710 --> 00:44.880
when you're working two jobs
to make ends meet?

00:44.880 --> 00:47.960
Even if you can make time,
it's dicey,

00:47.960 --> 00:50.250
because if someone sees you
running in the hood...
Hey!

00:50.250 --> 00:52.170
...they'll give you
something to run from.

00:52.170 --> 00:54.250
Despite our best efforts,

00:54.250 --> 00:57.040
the sugars is super common
with black folks.

00:57.040 --> 01:01.920
1.3 million black Americans are
currently living with it today.

01:01.920 --> 01:05.040
In fact, it's so common
that I already have it.

01:08.830 --> 01:11.210
♪♪

01:11.210 --> 01:14.040
Type 2 diabetes?

01:14.040 --> 01:15.420
But I feel fine.

01:15.420 --> 01:17.210
Well, many of the symptoms
are quite mild.

01:17.210 --> 01:18.790
Have you experienced
excessive thirst?

01:18.790 --> 01:20.460
Not necessarily.

01:20.460 --> 01:23.040
[ Gulping ]

01:23.040 --> 01:24.460
Hunger? Fatigue?

01:24.460 --> 01:25.540
No, not at all.

01:25.540 --> 01:28.750
♪♪

01:28.750 --> 01:30.250
Frequent urination?

01:30.250 --> 01:31.790
[ Toilet flushing ]
What'd you say, Doc?

01:31.790 --> 01:33.000
Frequent urination.

01:33.000 --> 01:34.620
Oh. Mnh-mnh.

01:34.620 --> 01:37.170
Some men even complain
of erectile dysfunction.

01:37.170 --> 01:38.670
Absolutely not.

01:38.670 --> 01:41.500
I'm fine in that area.
Tell him, Bow.

01:41.500 --> 01:43.580
Why is it taking you so long
to tell him?!

01:43.580 --> 01:45.040
He's fine.
[ Clears throat ]

01:45.040 --> 01:47.960
It's --
He is magnificent.

01:47.960 --> 01:49.330
[ Chuckles ]
You hear that?

01:49.330 --> 01:51.790
The best she's ever had.
Her words, not mine.

01:51.790 --> 01:52.960
I didn't say that.

01:52.960 --> 01:55.080
Perhaps we should get
back to your diagnosis.

01:55.080 --> 01:57.290
Listen, I know this is
not what you hoped for, Dre,

01:57.290 --> 01:59.920
but the good news is
diabetes is manageable.

01:59.920 --> 02:01.710
Okay.
Exactly.

02:01.710 --> 02:03.460
You'll just have to make
some adjustments.

02:03.460 --> 02:06.290
You'll want to exercise,
change your diet,

02:06.290 --> 02:09.040
monitor your blood sugar, and
start taking some medicine.

02:09.040 --> 02:11.080
Yeah.
These are all doable things.

02:11.080 --> 02:12.790
I mean, and I can help you
with the medication.

02:12.790 --> 02:15.290
I have been giving shots
since med school, so...

02:15.290 --> 02:16.880
Did you guys
practice on oranges?

02:16.880 --> 02:17.920
No. You know what?

02:17.920 --> 02:19.670
We used to practice
on hot dogs.

02:19.670 --> 02:21.290
Oh.
A boiled hot dog

02:21.290 --> 02:23.580
has the same snap
as human flesh.

02:23.580 --> 02:25.120
Yes, it does.

02:25.120 --> 02:27.080
And you know what else has
remarkably humanlike flesh?

02:27.080 --> 02:28.080
Don't do it.
Don't do it.

02:28.080 --> 02:29.080
Yeah, yeah, yeah.
Okay!

02:29.080 --> 02:29.920
Kiwis!
Kiwis!

02:29.920 --> 02:31.170
[ Both laugh ]

02:31.170 --> 02:32.710
'Cause of the hair!
The hair!

02:32.710 --> 02:34.670
Right? It's like a little --
It's like an arm.
Like an arm.

02:34.670 --> 02:37.250
Okay, this is worse
than the time I got diabetes.
Funny.

02:37.250 --> 02:39.380
Doctor, show her everything
that I need to know,

02:39.380 --> 02:41.250
and she'll demonstrate on
a piece of fruit for me later.

02:41.250 --> 02:42.330
Yeah.
I've got to get to work.

02:42.330 --> 02:44.170
Okay.
Bye, babe.

02:44.170 --> 02:46.290
Bye, babe. Mm.
See you later, Doc.

02:46.290 --> 02:47.670
[ Door closes ]
Oh, since we're sharing...

02:47.670 --> 02:49.880
Mm.
...my first year of residency,

02:49.880 --> 02:51.540
I may have killed a guy.

02:51.540 --> 02:54.670
Lemons
are also really good.

02:54.670 --> 02:56.710
Mm.
Lemons.

02:56.710 --> 02:58.420
♪♪

02:58.420 --> 02:59.880
Mmm.

02:59.880 --> 03:02.420
♪♪

03:02.420 --> 03:04.420
What's wrong?
Girl trouble?

03:04.420 --> 03:06.460
God, no.
It's Devante.

03:06.460 --> 03:08.380
I think
he's gunning for me.

03:08.380 --> 03:11.170
He's only 6 months old.
Impressive.

03:11.170 --> 03:12.880
I didn't start gunning for you
until we were 2.

03:12.880 --> 03:14.290
No, I'm serious.

03:14.290 --> 03:15.670
[ Engine revving ]

03:15.670 --> 03:16.880
[ Beeping ]

03:16.880 --> 03:19.210
At first, I thought
I was imagining things.

03:19.210 --> 03:23.080
[ Dramatic music plays ]

03:23.080 --> 03:24.920
But then,
i-it kept happening...

03:24.920 --> 03:27.290
Anybody see my ball?

03:27.290 --> 03:29.170
[ Dramatic music plays ]

03:29.170 --> 03:31.250
Now I realize
he wants to kill me.

03:32.960 --> 03:35.330
Okay, that last one
may have been a dream.

03:35.330 --> 03:39.250
But that doesn't change
the fact that Devante hates me.

03:39.250 --> 03:41.460
[ Sighs ]
What am I going to do?

03:41.460 --> 03:43.420
I've never been hated
before.

03:43.420 --> 03:44.460
I say embrace it.

03:44.460 --> 03:45.830
My haters give me life.

03:45.830 --> 03:47.880
Jack, babies don't hate.

03:47.880 --> 03:49.830
They're too busy
sleeping on clouds

03:49.830 --> 03:51.790
and laughing
with the angels.

03:51.790 --> 03:53.580
Not this baby.

03:53.580 --> 03:55.380
Hey, Devante.

03:55.380 --> 03:56.420
It's me, Jack.

03:56.420 --> 03:58.380
[ Devante cries ]

03:58.380 --> 03:59.830
Whoa.
Oh.

03:59.830 --> 04:02.620
I haven't seen that much hatred
in a baby's eyes since...

04:02.620 --> 04:03.620
Me.

04:03.620 --> 04:05.120
Well done, buddy.

04:05.120 --> 04:06.460
[ Chuckles ]

04:06.460 --> 04:08.120
[ Clink ]
I'm gonna build

04:08.120 --> 04:10.790
our Christmas-party
champagne tower with this.

04:10.790 --> 04:13.920
It's one of Grandpapa's rare,
antique, crystal glasses.

04:13.920 --> 04:15.790
Bored.
Oh, Dre!

04:15.790 --> 04:17.500
What say the doctor?

04:17.500 --> 04:20.250
-He say I got diabetes.
-Mm.

04:20.250 --> 04:21.750
-Oh.
-I thought you already had that,

04:21.750 --> 04:23.790
because of your [Whistles]

04:23.790 --> 04:24.920
your skin color.

04:24.920 --> 04:26.330
Stevens:
I'm not surprised either.

04:26.330 --> 04:28.750
Now, if you had old me
that you had good credit...

04:28.750 --> 04:30.290
[ Chuckles ]
-I have excellent credit.

04:30.290 --> 04:32.330
[ Chuckles ]
Good one, Dre.

04:32.330 --> 04:34.420
I do credit repairs now.

04:34.420 --> 04:36.670
How attached are you
to your fingerprints?

04:36.670 --> 04:38.540
Okay, look, guys,
this Dr. Reagan

04:38.540 --> 04:41.880
says many brave Americans
live every day with diabetes.

04:41.880 --> 04:43.750
Well, he lied.

04:43.750 --> 04:45.620
Diabetes is awful.

04:45.620 --> 04:47.040
It can take years
off your life.

04:47.040 --> 04:49.880
Years off my life?
Decades.

04:49.880 --> 04:52.000
And some people have to take
shots in their stomach.

04:52.000 --> 04:53.580
Josh: Or in their arm.

04:53.580 --> 04:54.920
That's how my uncle
took his diabetes medicine.

04:54.920 --> 04:56.790
Right in the vein.

04:56.790 --> 04:59.500
He said it makes you feel
like you're flying.

04:59.500 --> 05:01.960
I don't think
that was diabetes medicine.

05:01.960 --> 05:04.420
Mm. What else makes you
play trumpet like an angel?

05:04.420 --> 05:07.170
I'll give you
your shots, Dre.

05:07.170 --> 05:09.500
I'm like a ninja
when it comes to a needle.

05:09.500 --> 05:11.080
My aunt --
She was scared, too,

05:11.080 --> 05:13.250
so, every day,
I would sneak-attack her

05:13.250 --> 05:15.250
and shank her in the gut
with her insulin.

05:15.250 --> 05:16.920
Every day?

05:16.920 --> 05:18.330
Well, not every day.

05:18.330 --> 05:20.290
She skipped a day
once her foot got amputated.

05:20.290 --> 05:22.540
Yeah, diabetics
lose a lot of feet.

05:22.540 --> 05:23.710
A lot of feet?

05:23.710 --> 05:25.960
But, on the bright side,
if you do lose a foot,

05:25.960 --> 05:28.620
you can sell half
your sneaker collection.

05:28.620 --> 05:31.750
♪♪

05:31.750 --> 05:33.380
Am I winning him over?

05:33.380 --> 05:35.500
Does he like it?
No.

05:35.500 --> 05:36.620
No one.

05:36.620 --> 05:37.830
Likes it.

05:37.830 --> 05:39.670
When you.
Dance.

05:39.670 --> 05:42.750
You know what?
I have an idea.

05:42.750 --> 05:44.500
You've got
to make him jealous.

05:44.500 --> 05:47.330
Let him know that he's not
the only baby in your life.

05:47.330 --> 05:49.460
Here.
Bond with this.

05:49.460 --> 05:51.210
Hey!
Hm.

05:51.210 --> 05:52.460
You know
what'll make him jealous?

05:52.460 --> 05:53.500
Tickle that baby's belly.

05:53.500 --> 05:54.960
Tickle, tickle!

05:54.960 --> 05:56.380
[ Speaking baby talk ]

05:56.380 --> 05:58.120
Is it working?
Is Devante mad?

05:58.120 --> 06:00.000
No,
but that lady behind you is.

06:00.000 --> 06:03.420
♪♪

06:03.420 --> 06:05.500
Maybe if you stay off
your phone,

06:05.500 --> 06:06.670
then people won't have
the opportunity

06:06.670 --> 06:08.830
to snatch your baby!

06:08.830 --> 06:11.210
Don't try me, now.

06:11.210 --> 06:13.000
[ Door opens ]
[ Sighs ]

06:13.000 --> 06:14.880
Hey, there, dia-buddy!

06:14.880 --> 06:16.960
[ Laughs ]
That's a funny one.

06:16.960 --> 06:17.920
I mean...
[ Laughs ]

06:17.920 --> 06:19.000
It wasn't.

06:19.000 --> 06:21.620
Sweetie, it is time

06:21.620 --> 06:24.080
to check
your blood sugar levels.

06:24.080 --> 06:25.620
Here. I am going
to prick your finger.

06:25.620 --> 06:27.210
Okay. No, babe.
Oh, okay, okay.
Do -- Do --

06:27.210 --> 06:28.580
Babe, do we have to
right now?

06:28.580 --> 06:30.420
There -- There's
so many nerve endings.
Yes.

06:30.420 --> 06:32.830
Dr. Reagan
showed me everything.

06:32.830 --> 06:35.500
And it was actually kind of
like going back to med school,

06:35.500 --> 06:37.120
but without the bloody noses,

06:37.120 --> 06:39.580
'cause I used to put
so much pressure on myself.
Okay, cool.

06:39.580 --> 06:42.500
I can't wait for you to show me
this, but you know what?

06:42.500 --> 06:44.040
I've got to go buy
something online.

06:44.040 --> 06:45.580
Oh. Is it for me?

06:45.580 --> 06:48.000
No.

06:48.000 --> 06:49.920
Even in your lie,
you can't make it for me?

06:49.920 --> 06:52.620
Dre,
you've got to do this.

06:52.620 --> 06:55.500
Okay, babe, yes,
I know I have to do this.

06:55.500 --> 06:57.210
Okay.
And I'm gonna do it
by myself.

06:57.210 --> 06:58.250
You don't know
how to do it.

06:58.250 --> 06:59.750
I've got to learn sometime,
right?

06:59.750 --> 07:01.670
Yes.
I'm gonna learn by myself.

07:01.670 --> 07:03.210
Look.
Boop!

07:03.210 --> 07:04.290
Okay.
Got it.

07:04.290 --> 07:05.960
All right.
Got to put it in the finger.

07:05.960 --> 07:07.040
I'm gonna put it
in the finger.

07:07.040 --> 07:08.330
Right there.
Boop!
Okay.

07:08.330 --> 07:10.170
Boop!

07:10.170 --> 07:12.960
[ Suspenseful music plays ]

07:12.960 --> 07:14.170
[ Breathing deeply ]

07:14.170 --> 07:17.250
[ Whimpering ]

07:17.250 --> 07:19.830
[ Whimpering loudly ]

07:19.830 --> 07:21.670
What you doing out here --
giving birth?

07:21.670 --> 07:23.040
I wish.

07:23.040 --> 07:24.920
This is so much harder.

07:24.920 --> 07:27.460
Pops, I don't want
to prick my finger.
Let me see.

07:27.460 --> 07:29.830
Oh, you don't need to be
bothering with this mess.

07:29.830 --> 07:31.670
Come here.
Let me show you something.

07:31.670 --> 07:33.540
[ Mid-tempo music plays ]

07:33.540 --> 07:35.750
Once I kicked
prescription drugs to the curb

07:35.750 --> 07:38.540
and embraced natural healing,
my body cured itself.

07:38.540 --> 07:41.080
Last week,
I couldn't even walk.

07:41.080 --> 07:44.710
Now I am dancing the cha-cha!

07:44.710 --> 07:45.960
Mm!

07:45.960 --> 07:49.250
You hear that, son?
The cha-cha.

07:49.250 --> 07:50.710
Why didn't my doctor
tell me about this?

07:50.710 --> 07:51.830
'Cause there's no money
in the cure,

07:51.830 --> 07:53.580
only in the treatment.

07:53.580 --> 07:55.500
Also, there's also no money
in the restaurant business.

07:55.500 --> 07:57.670
That's why I sold
my Papa John's franchise.

07:57.670 --> 07:59.080
We were partners in that.

07:59.080 --> 08:00.750
Not on paper.

08:00.750 --> 08:04.290
Point is, diabetes doesn't
have to be a death sentence.

08:04.290 --> 08:05.790
You're saying
I can cure this?

08:05.790 --> 08:08.380
I'm not saying it.
The documentary's saying it.

08:08.380 --> 08:12.750
And a 56% Rotten Tomatoes score
doesn't lie.

08:12.750 --> 08:14.290
Hit "play."
[ Remote clicks ]

08:19.380 --> 08:21.040
Dre: That documentary
Pops showed me was the truth.

08:21.040 --> 08:23.170
Dr. Reagan just wanted
to manage my diabetes.
Ahh.

08:23.170 --> 08:24.460
I was gonna cure it.

08:24.460 --> 08:25.620
Son.
Mm?

08:25.620 --> 08:26.960
What is that?

08:26.960 --> 08:29.330
It's Rare Earth Seltzer --

08:29.330 --> 08:31.710
antiviral,
anti-inflammatory,

08:31.710 --> 08:33.670
and it regenerates
cell growth.

08:33.670 --> 08:36.000
It looks like tap water
from Flint, Michigan.

08:36.000 --> 08:39.460
Oh. And I also take six
of these four times a day

08:39.460 --> 08:40.460
to help me detox.

08:40.460 --> 08:42.500
What a coincidence.

08:42.500 --> 08:44.710
I take six of these
to help me re-tox.

08:44.710 --> 08:46.040
[ Laughs ]
All right.

08:46.040 --> 08:48.040
That dirty Flint water
tasted bad,

08:48.040 --> 08:49.750
but put me on the right track.

08:49.750 --> 08:52.460
So four sweat lodge sessions,
two colonics,

08:52.460 --> 08:54.710
and one heavy metal detox
later,

08:54.710 --> 08:58.330
I knew I was that much closer
to curing my diabetes.

08:58.330 --> 09:01.040
These are the only thing
I got in my grandpa's will.

09:01.040 --> 09:02.670
My cousins,
they got the business,

09:02.670 --> 09:05.670
the houses, the cars,
but I got these glasses

09:05.670 --> 09:07.920
he swore
were not Nazi war loot.

09:07.920 --> 09:10.210
[ Chuckles ]

09:10.210 --> 09:12.750
Rachel, what --
What'd I say?

09:12.750 --> 09:13.920
Bacon-wrapped shrimp?

09:13.920 --> 09:15.460
-Ooh.
-Ah.

09:15.460 --> 09:17.750
Yes, I will.
More like dead
swine-wrapped bottom feeder.

09:17.750 --> 09:19.580
Dre, what is wrong with you?

09:19.580 --> 09:23.040
These are delicious
deep-water sea buds.

09:23.040 --> 09:24.670
Respect your temple,
like I do.

09:24.670 --> 09:27.080
I don't put that garbage
in my body.

09:27.080 --> 09:29.460
I don't put anything
in my body.

09:29.460 --> 09:31.580
Dre, you're not eating food?
You love food.

09:31.580 --> 09:33.330
That's the only thing
you took out of your office

09:33.330 --> 09:35.170
when the fire alarm
went off.
Not anymore.

09:35.170 --> 09:38.210
Three wellness blogs and
an online certified health coach

09:38.210 --> 09:41.330
showed me
that fasting cures diseases.

09:41.330 --> 09:44.960
And in just two short days, you
can renew your immune system.

09:44.960 --> 09:47.540
Mm.
I used to fast a kid.

09:47.540 --> 09:49.670
I would eat a big meal
in November,

09:49.670 --> 09:52.830
then wouldn't eat again
until I woke up in the spring.

09:52.830 --> 09:55.120
Wait a minute.
That was bears.
Mm-hmm.

09:55.120 --> 09:57.250
[ Whispering ] Stop talking
about bears in public.

09:57.250 --> 09:58.830
Stop talking about bears
in public.

09:58.830 --> 10:00.670
Stop talking
about bears in public.

10:00.670 --> 10:04.710
Okay, Dre, so, you're gonna cure
a chronic disease by fasting?

10:04.710 --> 10:06.120
Yup. Yeah.
Uh-huh.

10:06.120 --> 10:07.290
Better than taking pills.

10:07.290 --> 10:08.500
I need all my pills.

10:08.500 --> 10:09.750
Why?

10:09.750 --> 10:11.750
What does that do for you?

10:11.750 --> 10:13.580
Well, it's either gonna
rev me up or calm me down.

10:13.580 --> 10:14.790
Just got to spin the wheel.

10:14.790 --> 10:16.670
It's, uh --

10:16.670 --> 10:19.460
It's so simple
that it's crazy.
Mm-hmm.

10:19.460 --> 10:22.380
When our bodies talk to us,
we just need to listen.

10:22.380 --> 10:23.960
You know what I mean?
I don't, Dre.

10:23.960 --> 10:25.750
And a matter of fact,
I am gonna outsource

10:25.750 --> 10:27.580
this entire office
to India

10:27.580 --> 10:30.040
unless I get
a crab-stuffed mushroom cap!

10:30.040 --> 10:32.000
You, Santa's helper,
come here!

10:33.540 --> 10:35.830
[ Sighs ]

10:35.830 --> 10:37.620
Oh, man, it's hot.

10:39.210 --> 10:41.920
I need something to drink.

10:41.920 --> 10:45.040
[ Scoffs ]
Look at this yearbook love --

10:45.040 --> 10:47.170
"You da man,"
"you da best."

10:47.170 --> 10:49.290
But Devante
would never write that.

10:49.290 --> 10:51.500
He doesn't even like me.
[ Sighs ]

10:51.500 --> 10:53.880
Can I let you in
on a little secret?

10:57.290 --> 10:59.210
Lots of people
don't like me.

11:00.460 --> 11:03.540
Yeah, but --
but what's the secret?

11:03.540 --> 11:05.790
See, Jack,

11:05.790 --> 11:08.380
you have
a tender, unblemished heart,

11:08.380 --> 11:11.170
while mine is
rough and callused

11:11.170 --> 11:13.920
from familial neglect,
ridicule, and --

11:13.920 --> 11:15.330
Get on with it, Long Head.

11:15.330 --> 11:16.830
See?

11:16.830 --> 11:18.580
That didn't even faze me.

11:18.580 --> 11:19.960
And if you follow me,

11:19.960 --> 11:23.580
soon, horrible abuse
won't bother you either.

11:23.580 --> 11:25.000
But how?

11:25.000 --> 11:26.500
[ Suspenseful music plays ]

11:26.500 --> 11:28.000
Hello, friend.

11:28.000 --> 11:30.960
Oh, no, no, no.
There has to be another way.

11:30.960 --> 11:32.830
Junior:
You can do it, Jack.

11:32.830 --> 11:35.000
Build that scar.

11:35.000 --> 11:36.120
Okay.

11:37.380 --> 11:38.830
[ Clears throat ]

11:38.830 --> 11:41.120
Mom had Devante
to replace you.

11:41.120 --> 11:43.290
You're
her biggest disappointment.

11:43.290 --> 11:45.920
[ Sighs ] Nothing
you haven't said before.

11:45.920 --> 11:48.920
All that matters
is that I'm alive.

11:48.920 --> 11:52.040
Um, well, then...

11:52.040 --> 11:54.790
you got a pity invite
to Cooper's party,

11:54.790 --> 11:57.880
and everyone hung out after
and didn't even tell you.

11:57.880 --> 11:59.580
So?

11:59.580 --> 12:01.380
That doesn't bother me.

12:01.380 --> 12:04.460
Carla said it's because
your stories meander.

12:04.460 --> 12:07.000
But Vanessa said it's
because you're a bad dancer.

12:07.000 --> 12:09.040
[ Breathes sharply ]
Vanessa said that?

12:09.040 --> 12:10.920
You're the slow reader
in class,

12:10.920 --> 12:13.040
and everyone texts about it
when it's your turn.

12:13.040 --> 12:14.080
I'll tell Miss Davis.

12:14.080 --> 12:15.330
She started the group chat.

12:15.330 --> 12:16.920
Wow.

12:16.920 --> 12:18.880
Feels pretty bad, huh?

12:18.880 --> 12:20.080
Bet you want to cry
to your mommy.

12:20.080 --> 12:21.330
Hmm?
Hmm?

12:23.380 --> 12:25.210
I have no mommy.

12:28.460 --> 12:30.920
I'm ready
to go break that baby.

12:30.920 --> 12:32.750
♪♪

12:32.750 --> 12:34.040
Hi, there.

12:35.040 --> 12:36.420
Connor: Hi. Hello.

12:36.420 --> 12:37.540
I'm gonna take it
from all the pictures

12:37.540 --> 12:39.380
that Charlie has of you
on his phone

12:39.380 --> 12:41.580
that you are Dre's wife.
Yeah, I-I am.

12:41.580 --> 12:43.080
Whoo-hoo!

12:43.080 --> 12:45.000
I think I just figured out
what this pill does.

12:45.000 --> 12:46.880
Gonna need a little water.
Mmm.

12:46.880 --> 12:48.040
Oh, okay.
I'll just get...

12:48.040 --> 12:49.420
Oh, my.
Okay. Okay.

12:49.420 --> 12:50.460
Wow.

12:50.460 --> 12:52.540
Um, do you know
where Dre is?

12:52.540 --> 12:53.960
Yeah, he's over there.
He's sick, man.

12:53.960 --> 12:55.420
He's sick.
[ Chuckles ]

12:55.420 --> 12:56.670
I'm feeling
a little bit dancy right now.

12:56.670 --> 12:58.080
Would you like to dance
with me a little bit?

12:58.080 --> 12:59.290
[ Breathes deeply ]

12:59.290 --> 13:01.580
Ooh.

13:01.580 --> 13:02.880
Hey, Dre.
Mm?

13:02.880 --> 13:04.670
Honey, are you okay?
Wha--

13:04.670 --> 13:06.960
Oh, I'm fine.

13:06.960 --> 13:08.920
Are you okay?

13:08.920 --> 13:11.170
'Cause you're really blurry.

13:11.170 --> 13:12.620
Come here, baby.

13:12.620 --> 13:14.120
Mm-hmm.

13:14.120 --> 13:17.380
Okay, Dre,
your pulse is racing.

13:17.380 --> 13:18.880
Did you take
your medication?

13:18.880 --> 13:21.080
I don't need it.
I'm doing fine without it.

13:21.080 --> 13:22.540
I'm fasting.
Okay.

13:22.540 --> 13:23.710
You're about to pass out.

13:23.710 --> 13:25.670
I am not going to pass out.

13:25.670 --> 13:27.120
Yeah, okay, yeah.
Yes, you are.
I'm passing out.

13:27.120 --> 13:27.880
Oh, God. Oh, God!
Gone.

13:27.880 --> 13:29.120
Oh! Oh!

13:31.000 --> 13:32.460
Oh, my God!
Oh, my God!

13:32.460 --> 13:34.120
Okay. Dre? Dre?
Aah!

13:34.120 --> 13:37.040
Oh, no.
Oh, Grandpapa's glasses!

13:37.040 --> 13:38.120
Oh, my God.
No, no.

13:38.120 --> 13:39.620
Honey.

13:39.620 --> 13:41.080
Oh. Oh, wait.

13:41.080 --> 13:42.620
M-My tower's over there.
It --

13:42.620 --> 13:43.670
[ Suspenseful music plays ]

13:43.670 --> 13:45.120
Charlie.
No, no, no.

13:45.120 --> 13:47.290
No, no, no, no, no, no!

13:47.290 --> 13:49.500
[ Gasps ]
Oh, thank God.

13:49.500 --> 13:50.710
Does anybody want
to kiss me?

13:50.710 --> 13:52.040
Anybody?
It's okay.

13:52.040 --> 13:53.830
Just step forward.
No, Connor!

13:53.830 --> 13:55.710
Con-- No!

13:55.710 --> 13:57.330
[ Crowd gasping ]

13:57.330 --> 14:00.920
Whoo!
Who wants to kiss me?!

14:04.580 --> 14:06.120
♪♪

14:06.120 --> 14:09.960
I can't believe that you haven't
been taking your medication.

14:09.960 --> 14:11.290
I don't need it.
What?!

14:11.290 --> 14:13.040
All right, I'm gonna cure
my diabetes naturally.

14:13.040 --> 14:14.330
I'm gonna do the cha-cha.

14:14.330 --> 14:16.670
Diabetes isn't curable.

14:16.670 --> 14:19.170
We can help manage it with
proper diet and exercise,

14:19.170 --> 14:21.210
but you need to take
your medicine!

14:21.210 --> 14:23.500
Of course
you would say that...

14:23.500 --> 14:24.830
Doctor.

14:24.830 --> 14:29.790
Please do not say "doctor"
like I'm the enemy, okay?

14:29.790 --> 14:31.080
I am your partner in this.

14:31.080 --> 14:32.960
You're just a passenger,
okay?

14:32.960 --> 14:34.500
I'm the one
that's dealing with this,

14:34.500 --> 14:36.120
and I'm gonna need you
to support

14:36.120 --> 14:37.500
the way
that I want to heal myself.

14:37.500 --> 14:42.460
Complications from untreated
diabetes can kill you.

14:42.460 --> 14:44.540
You could have
a heart attack or a stroke.

14:44.540 --> 14:46.330
Have you thought about
what happens to your family?

14:46.330 --> 14:47.500
Or your kids?

14:47.500 --> 14:48.750
Or are you just thinking
about yourself?

14:48.750 --> 14:50.420
That's not fair.

14:50.420 --> 14:52.460
You know I always
just think about myself.

14:52.460 --> 14:53.540
Oh, my God. Okay.

14:53.540 --> 14:55.830
♪♪

14:55.830 --> 14:58.960
Jack: I want some orange juice
and some toast.

14:58.960 --> 15:01.790
[ Indistinct conversation
in distance ]

15:01.790 --> 15:04.880
♪♪

15:04.880 --> 15:06.880
Can I get some egg, please?
-Junior, you want some tea?

15:06.880 --> 15:08.330
Do you want some tea?
-Yeah, can I get a cup, please?

15:08.330 --> 15:10.290
-Oh, I'm fine.
-Hey, morning, fam.

15:10.290 --> 15:12.420
Junior, you want fruit?
Oh, yes, please, Mom.

15:12.420 --> 15:13.790
Can you please
leave it there?
What's for breakfast?

15:13.790 --> 15:14.920
Sure, sure, sure.
All righty.

15:14.920 --> 15:15.960
How about you?
You want fruit?

15:15.960 --> 15:17.170
-Of course. Thank you.
-Mom.

15:17.170 --> 15:18.790
-Oh, of course.
-They can't hear you.

15:18.790 --> 15:20.750
You're dead.
-Here. You want some tea?

15:20.750 --> 15:23.210
Told you to take
your medicine, dummy.

15:23.210 --> 15:25.000
You told me
not to take my medicine!

15:25.000 --> 15:26.790
Oh, don't listen to me.

15:26.790 --> 15:30.120
I'm just the crazy old man
that lives in your backyard.
I --

15:30.120 --> 15:31.960
Mom, when is New Daddy
coming home?

15:31.960 --> 15:33.790
Oh!
Not soon enough, sweetie.

15:33.790 --> 15:35.380
"New Daddy"?

15:35.380 --> 15:36.580
Bow remarried?

15:36.580 --> 15:38.960
She mourned for you
as long as she could,

15:38.960 --> 15:41.750
but the children
needed a father.

15:41.750 --> 15:42.830
How long did she mourn?

15:42.830 --> 15:44.290
A couple of days.

15:44.290 --> 15:45.710
New Daddy's home!
Together: Yes!

15:45.710 --> 15:47.580
He is! Yay!

15:47.580 --> 15:49.120
Rick Fox?!

15:49.120 --> 15:51.120
I know she didn't!

15:51.120 --> 15:53.380
He's an incredibly
attractive man, son.

15:53.380 --> 15:56.170
Yeah --
Dude was a Laker
and a Celtic.

15:56.170 --> 15:58.500
Hey!
And he's not dead
from a manageable illness.

15:58.500 --> 16:01.380
I am so glad I'm
the only child in this family

16:01.380 --> 16:03.790
who's not genetically
predisposed to diabetes.

16:03.790 --> 16:06.250
I always knew
Rick Fox was her real daddy.

16:06.250 --> 16:07.880
Everybody knew that.

16:07.880 --> 16:09.040
I mean, look at their faces,

16:09.040 --> 16:10.620
and then look
at your potato face.

16:10.620 --> 16:12.540
-Here you go.
-Thank you.

16:12.540 --> 16:15.460
Since Dad died, it's like
the hatred in my heart

16:15.460 --> 16:17.670
was buried with him
in that little coffee can.

16:17.670 --> 16:20.210
-Oh.
-Coffee can?! No!

16:20.210 --> 16:22.830
At least spring
for a Costco coffin!

16:22.830 --> 16:24.250
I love you, Rick Dad!

16:24.250 --> 16:25.750
-Get in here.
-Yay!

16:25.750 --> 16:26.830
-Yes, yes.
-Oh!

16:26.830 --> 16:28.000
-Aww!
-Aww!

16:28.000 --> 16:30.120
[ Laughs ] Yeah!

16:30.120 --> 16:31.670
Ditto, New Pop.

16:31.670 --> 16:33.920
I finally know what
it feels like to be loved.

16:33.920 --> 16:35.080
Together: Aww.

16:35.080 --> 16:36.420
Permission to hug you,
sir?

16:36.420 --> 16:38.460
You don't need permission...

16:38.460 --> 16:39.830
son.

16:39.830 --> 16:41.000
Together: Aww!

16:41.000 --> 16:42.750
Junior?

16:42.750 --> 16:44.830
I'm so glad my dad died.
What?!

16:44.830 --> 16:45.830
-Me too.
-Mm-hmm.

16:45.830 --> 16:47.540
Yeah. Me too.

16:47.540 --> 16:49.460
Aww! Aww!

16:49.460 --> 16:51.170
Mwah!

16:51.170 --> 16:52.330
Oh!
Oh!

16:52.330 --> 16:54.170
-Oh, Rick Fox!
-Oh!

16:54.170 --> 16:55.540
[ Laughs ]

16:55.540 --> 16:57.210
Oh!
-This is so great.

16:57.210 --> 16:58.500
Shall we?
Yes.

16:58.500 --> 16:59.750
Let's do it.
[ Chuckling ] Yes.

16:59.750 --> 17:01.250
-Oh.
-Bye.

17:01.250 --> 17:03.580
[ Voice breaking ]
Not in my bed.

17:03.580 --> 17:05.670
[ Breathes deeply ]
Definitely in your bed.

17:05.670 --> 17:06.670
[ Sobs ]

17:06.670 --> 17:09.170
Nooooo!

17:14.210 --> 17:16.210
[ Sighs ]

17:16.210 --> 17:18.250
Rainbow: Hey, Jack, can
you watch Devante for a minute?

17:18.250 --> 17:19.500
Yeah, I will.

17:19.500 --> 17:20.790
Look, you little baby.

17:20.790 --> 17:22.330
You can hate me
all you want,

17:22.330 --> 17:24.420
but you're stuck with me,
because I love you!

17:24.420 --> 17:26.500
You don't like me mad?

17:26.500 --> 17:27.750
Oh, you going to tell?

17:27.750 --> 17:29.420
[ Scoffs ] Try it.

17:29.420 --> 17:31.540
No one's going to listen
to a little baby.

17:31.540 --> 17:33.790
You're a little baby
that can't talk

17:33.790 --> 17:35.920
and doesn't know
baby sign language

17:35.920 --> 17:37.120
because Mom is too lazy

17:37.120 --> 17:38.830
to keep up
with modern parenting trends!

17:38.830 --> 17:40.460
[ Breathes deeply ]

17:40.460 --> 17:43.790
I'm sorry
to serve you so hard,

17:43.790 --> 17:44.960
but you asked for it.

17:48.040 --> 17:50.710
[ Laughs ]

17:50.710 --> 17:52.670
Oh, you think
that's funny, huh?

17:52.670 --> 17:54.290
[ Laughs ]

17:54.290 --> 17:56.500
Wait.

17:56.500 --> 17:58.380
You thought
that was funny?

18:00.920 --> 18:03.540
[ Laughs ]

18:03.540 --> 18:05.330
I made you laugh.

18:05.330 --> 18:07.120
Maybe you don't hate me
after all.

18:08.710 --> 18:11.290
See? I told you.

18:11.290 --> 18:14.460
If you'd just be patient,
he'd warm up to you.

18:14.460 --> 18:16.500
You told me to form
a scar on my heart.

18:16.500 --> 18:18.290
I did,
but all that matters

18:18.290 --> 18:20.960
is that little Devante
"wuves" you.

18:20.960 --> 18:22.000
Ow!

18:22.000 --> 18:23.000
[ Crying ]

18:23.000 --> 18:24.380
He bit me.

18:24.380 --> 18:26.290
I thought we were cool.

18:26.290 --> 18:27.960
Oh, no.

18:27.960 --> 18:30.290
I've lost him.

18:30.290 --> 18:33.210
Looks like there's only room
in his heart for one of us.

18:33.210 --> 18:34.830
Isn't that right,
Devante?

18:34.830 --> 18:36.290
We don't like Junior.

18:36.290 --> 18:37.920
We don't like him.

18:37.920 --> 18:39.830
♪♪

18:39.830 --> 18:41.920
Hey, babe.
Hey.

18:41.920 --> 18:44.380
Um...

18:44.380 --> 18:46.000
can you help me check
my blood sugar?

18:46.000 --> 18:48.380
I-I may be
a little scared of this.

18:48.380 --> 18:50.790
Of course, sweetie.

18:50.790 --> 18:53.080
You know, I'm not just your
partner -- I am a doctor.

18:53.080 --> 18:55.750
What?!
You're a doctor?

18:55.750 --> 18:57.620
Oh, come on, Dre.

18:57.620 --> 18:58.880
Sweetie,
I know you're scared.

18:58.880 --> 19:00.500
[ Device beeps ]

19:00.500 --> 19:03.540
But [Sighs] you got to come
to me with this stuff.

19:03.540 --> 19:04.920
Mm-hmm.

19:04.920 --> 19:06.040
We're together in this,

19:06.040 --> 19:07.920
and I'm gonna support you,
no matter what.

19:07.920 --> 19:10.290
I bet you say that
to Rick Fox, too.

19:10.290 --> 19:12.330
What? [ Chuckles ]
I'm sorry, babe.

19:12.330 --> 19:14.830
I have weird dreams
on an empty stomach.
Mm-hmm.

19:14.830 --> 19:18.000
I guess I'm probably afraid
admitting that I'm a diabetic,

19:18.000 --> 19:19.580
because it means
I'll be a diabetic...
[ Click ]

19:19.580 --> 19:22.080
for the...
rest of my life.

19:22.080 --> 19:24.250
Is that it?
Yeah.

19:24.250 --> 19:25.920
That's what
I was afraid of?

19:25.920 --> 19:27.670
Yep.
Oh, babe.

19:27.670 --> 19:29.830
If I can handle that...

19:29.830 --> 19:31.710
I can handle
my injections.

19:31.710 --> 19:35.250
See, Dre?

19:35.250 --> 19:37.290
This does not have
to define you.

19:37.290 --> 19:39.670
When people think
of Andre Johnson,

19:39.670 --> 19:41.460
they're gonna think...

19:41.460 --> 19:43.210
great shoe collection...

19:43.210 --> 19:44.420
Mm-hmm.
One of the best.

19:44.420 --> 19:45.830
...talented ad man...

19:45.830 --> 19:47.210
Oh, the best.

19:47.210 --> 19:49.620
...beautiful wife...
She a hottie.

19:49.620 --> 19:51.500
...smart wife...
Oh.
I'll give her that.

19:51.500 --> 19:54.250
How did he get that wife?!

19:54.250 --> 19:55.830
Okay, slow your roll.

19:55.830 --> 19:58.880
Look, Dre,
the important thing to know

19:58.880 --> 20:03.420
is that diabetes
is not gonna "dia beat-us."

20:03.420 --> 20:05.500
[ Laughs ]

20:05.500 --> 20:07.920
Dia--
How long have you been
holding on to that one?

20:07.920 --> 20:10.710
[ Laughing ] Oh, my God.

20:10.710 --> 20:12.670
For so long.

20:12.670 --> 20:15.210
But it's never been
the right time, Dre.

20:15.210 --> 20:17.710
And I can tell
by the look on your face

20:17.710 --> 20:19.080
that now isn't either.

20:19.080 --> 20:22.420
But, my darling,
I have about 10 more.

20:22.420 --> 20:24.920
It's do or diabetes!
[ Laughs ]

20:28.880 --> 20:30.170
Good news, guys.

20:30.170 --> 20:31.580
We just got
the Right Guard account.

20:31.580 --> 20:32.790
And I would like
to introduce you...
All right!

20:32.790 --> 20:33.790
...to our new spokesman.

20:33.790 --> 20:35.040
Mm.

20:35.040 --> 20:36.210
-[ Chuckles ]
-All right.

20:37.330 --> 20:40.210
First my home,
and now my work?

20:40.210 --> 20:43.670
When is it enough for you,
Rick Fox?

20:43.670 --> 20:44.790
I'm sorry.
Do I know you?

20:44.790 --> 20:46.580
No, you don't know me.

20:46.580 --> 20:48.620
You ain't gonna never
know me.

20:48.620 --> 20:50.000
Well, I think
you're actually gonna get

20:50.000 --> 20:51.380
to know each other
quite well,

20:51.380 --> 20:53.290
because you're the lead
on this account, Dre.

20:53.290 --> 20:56.210
And Connor's
on the team, too.

20:56.210 --> 20:58.080
-Yeah, I am!
-Oh, my God.

20:58.080 --> 21:00.000
Connor, are --
are you okay?

21:00.000 --> 21:01.710
Nope. No.

21:01.710 --> 21:03.620
Whatever I took
has not worn off, all right?

21:03.620 --> 21:05.330
I've done irreparable harm
to myself.

21:05.330 --> 21:08.120
[ Laughs ] Whoo!
